        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-03-17 09:25:03.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-7813 lod: inherit pool from parent if unspecified",
        "message": "LU-7813 lod: inherit pool from parent if unspecified\n\nIf the OST pool is not set in a specific file layout, but the pool\nis set on the parent directory, inherit the pool from the parent.\n\nThis makes OST pools much more usable, since the expectation is that\nfiles created in a directory with a pool set will be part of the pool,\neven if there was a need to set explicit striping for the file.\n\nIf the specified stripe size is not a multiple of LOV_MIN_STRIPE_SIZE,\ninstead of truncating it to LOV_MIN_STRIPE_SIZE, round it to the\nnearest multiple instead.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I4747ec3aa829fa9beec50e4c85c5238b2f4f5ff7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
